# Usage Example Generator

## Overview
Generate clear, practical usage examples for code documentation.

## Activation
Activates when user mentions "usage examples", "code samples", or "show how to use".

## Instructions

1. Analyze the function/class/API
2. Create examples showing:
   - Basic usage
   - Common use cases
   - Edge cases
   - Error handling
   - Advanced patterns

3. Make examples:
   - Self-contained (copy-paste ready)
   - Realistic (real-world scenarios)
   - Progressive (simple â†’ complex)

## Examples

**Input:** "examples for this fetch wrapper"

**Output:**
```javascript
// Basic GET request
const users = await api.get('/users');

// GET with query parameters
const filtered = await api.get('/users', {
  params: { role: 'admin', active: true }
});

// POST with body
const newUser = await api.post('/users', {
  body: { name: 'John', email: 'john@example.com' }
});

// With error handling
try {
  const data = await api.get('/users/123');
} catch (error) {
  if (error.status === 404) {
    console.log('User not found');
  }
}
```
